summary: This document consists of four evidence custody forms (OIG Form III-234/1) from the U.S. Department of Justice Office of the Inspector General. The forms record the seizure of various items of property, including a hard drive, audio equipment, and documents, from unspecified locations. The forms document the chain of custody for the seized evidence.
keyFacts: The document is a series of official DOJ OIG evidence custody forms used to track seized property.
Multiple items were seized, including a hard drive, Diamond Audio equipment, and various documents.
The forms document a detailed chain of custody, recording dates, times, and personnel involved in handling the evidence.
The specific locations from which property was seized and the names of involved personnel are largely illegible or redacted in the provided text.
